section.section:
Each nursing home shall establish a quality assurance committee and shall include at least the following members:
The nursing home administrator;
The director of nursing;
The medical director;
A social worker;
A licensed dietitian; and
A geriatric nursing assistant.

The quality assurance committee shall:
Meet at least monthly;
Maintain records of all quality assurance activities;
Keep records of committee meetings that shall be available to the Department during any on-site visit; and
Prepare monthly reports that shall be presented to the ombudsman, the resident's council, and the family council.

Each nursing home shall establish a written quality assurance plan that:
Includes procedures for concurrent review for all residents;
Provides criteria that routinely monitors nursing care including medication administration, prevention of decubitus ulcers, dehydration and malnutrition, nutritional status and weight loss or gain, accidents and injuries, unexpected deaths, changes in mental or psychological status, and any other data necessary to monitor quality of care;
Includes methods to identify and correct problems; and
Is readily available to nursing home residents and their families, guardians, or surrogate decision makers.
